<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>They've been busy shooting the upcoming police drama.</p>

<p>And Catherine Tyldesley and co-star Noel Clarke continued to film new series Viewpoint in Manchester on Thursday. </p>

<p>The former Coronation Street star, 37, looked glamorous in a brown leather-look midi skirt with a lighter coloured shirt tucked in.</p>

<p>Glamorous: Catherine Tyldesley continued to film new series Viewpoint in Manchester on Thursday</p>

<p>Although Catherine made sure she wrapped up warm in a thick grey padded long-length padded jacket and shearling-lined ankle boots to shoot scenes.</p>

<p>Catherine styled her brunette locks into a curly blow-dried hairdo and added a slick of glamorous make-up for filming. </p>

<p>The star appeared to get stuck into shooting as she was later seen putting on an animated display inside a restaurant for one scene.</p>

<p>Catherine was joined by co-stars Dominic Allburn and Alexandra Roach, who will be taking on one of the lead roles as Zoe Sterling, inside the eatery.</p>

<p>Cast: The former Coronation Street star, 37, was joined by co-star Noel Clarke on set (L-R) </p>

<p>Busy bee: Catherine was joined by co-stars Dominic Allburn and Alexandra Roach, who will be taking on one of the lead roles as Zoe Sterling, inside the eatery </p>

<p>Keeping warm! Although Catherine made sure she wrapped up warm in a thick grey padded long-length padded jacket and shearling-lined ankle boots to shoot scenes</p>

<p>In one scene, Catherine as her character held Dominic's hand during a meal for the drama where he was later seen getting up and observing a missing poster sign.</p>

<p>Elsewhere on set, show lead Noel Clarke, 44, who will take on the role of surveillance detective, DC Martin King, was spotted as he filmed scenes with Bronagh Waugh.</p>

<p>Noel wore a pair of skinny jeans with a grey polo neck T-shirt and burgundy cropped jacket, he finished his look with black trainers and a rucksack. </p>

<p>Agitated: In one scene, actor Dominic, as his character, appeared agitated when he saw a missing person sign </p>

<p>And... action! The star appeared to get stuck into shooting as she was later seen putting on an animated display inside a restaurant for one scene</p>

<p>Tense? In one scene, Catherine and Dominic as their characters appeared tense </p>

<p>Bronagh, 37, was seen wearing a pair of brown combat trousers with a grey shirt, leather jacket and burgundy biker boots.</p>

<p>The star, who left her fiery red curly locks loose, also wrapped up warmly for filming in a matching grey padded jacket to Catherine.   </p>

<p>Viewpoint, one of the ITV's first post-lockdown series, recently saw production suspended after a positive coronavirus test on set. </p>

<p>Career: This is just one of the new TV projects Catherine has been involved with since quitting her role of Eva Price on Coronation Street in 2018</p>

<p>A scuffle? In a different scene, Dominic appeared to be in a scuffle with another character </p>

<p>Leading star: Elsewhere on set, show lead Noel Clarke, 44, who will take on the role of surveillance detective, DC Martin King, was spotted as he filmed scenes with Bronagh Waugh</p>

<p>But things were swiftly back to normal thanks to the safety protocols in place with the stars back on set and filming this week.</p>

<p>Viewpoint, which is headed up by Fleabag director Harry Bradbeer, follows a tense police surveillance investigation into a close Manchester community.</p>

<p>Noel will take on the role of surveillance detective, DC Martin King, as he investigates missing primary school teacher, Gemma Hillman, played by Amy Wren. </p>

<p>Casual: Noel wore a pair of skinny jeans with a grey polo neck T-shirt and burgundy cropped jacket, he finished his look with black trainers and a rucksack</p>

<p>Star: Bronagh Waugh, 37, was seen wearing a pair of brown combat trousers with a grey shirt, leather jacket and burgundy biker boots  </p>

<p>Filming: Actress Erin Shanagher was also spotted on set during filming </p>

<p>This is just one of the new TV projects Catherine has been involved with since quitting her role of Eva Price on Coronation Street in 2018.</p>

<p>Catherine's outing comes after she furiously took to Instagram on Monday to call out a social media troll who cruelly claimed she has 'big fat legs'. </p>

<p>Referencing her strict workout schedule, the actress proved she's proud of how far she's come from being a size 22 teen as she hit back with: 'I guarantee I could deadlift or squat your entire body weight, my love.'  </p>

<p>Cast: Alexandra Roach, who will be taking on one of the lead roles as Zoe Sterling, was spotted filming on Thursday </p>

<p>Keeping warm! The actress made sure she kept warm with shearling-lined boots and a hot beverage </p>

<p>The Strictly Come Dancing star addressed the naysayer directly as she said: 'It's not often your Auntie Cath gets trolled, I'm very lucky like that. I've got lots of wonderful, positive people in my life.</p>

<p>'You do get the occasional twonk, so to the guy yesterday who said I had 'big fat legs', babes, I've been training these legs for seven years. This s**t don't wobble, and I guarantee I could deadlift or squat your entire body weight, my love.</p>

<p>'So things just got really awkward, really fast, didn't they? God bless ya, darling. Find the light, come on.'  </p>

<p>Back to it! Viewpoint, one of the ITV's first post-lockdown series, recently saw production suspended after a positive coronavirus test on set but it has since resumed filming </p>
